<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="AbstractParser.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PHP/CodeSniffer/CommentParser/AbstractParser.php"><variable citdl="string" line="17" name="error" /><scope attributes="abstract" doc="Parses doc comments.&#10;&#10;This abstract parser handles the following tags:&#10;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10; &lt;li&gt;The short description and the long description&lt;/li&gt;&#10; &lt;li&gt;@see&lt;/li&gt;&#10; &lt;li&gt;@link&lt;/li&gt;&#10; &lt;li&gt;@deprecated&lt;/li&gt;&#10; &lt;li&gt;@since&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&#10;Extending classes should implement the getAllowedTags() method to return the&#10;tags that they wish to process, omitting the tags that this base class&#10;processes. When one of these tags in encountered, the process&amp;lt;tag_name&amp;gt;&#10;method is called on that class. For example, if a parser's getAllowedTags()&#10;method returns \@param as one of its tags, the processParam method will be&#10;called so that the parser can process such a tag.&#10;&#10;The method is passed the tokens that comprise this tag. The tokens array&#10;includes the whitespace that exists between the tokens, as separate tokens.&#10;It's up to the method to create a element that implements the DocElement&#10;interface, which should be returned. The AbstractDocElement class is a helper&#10;class that can be used to handle most of the parsing of the tokens into their&#10;individual sub elements. It requires that you construct it with the element&#10;previous to the element currently being processed, which can be acquired&#10;with the protected $previousElement class member of this class.&#10;&#10;@category  PHP&#10;@package   PHP_CodeSniffer&#10;@author    Greg Sherwood &lt;gsherwood@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@author    Marc McIntyre &lt;mmcintyre@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@copyright 2006-2012 Squiz Pty Ltd (ABN 77 084 670 600)&#10;@license   https://github.com/squizlabs/PHP_CodeSniffer/blob/master/licence.txt BSD Licence&#10;@version   Release: 1.4.6&#10;@link      http://pear.php.net/package/PHP_CodeSniffer" ilk="class" line="69" lineend="682" name="PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_AbstractParser"><variable attributes="protected" citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_CommentElement" doc="The comment element that appears in the doc comment.&#10;&#10;@var PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_CommentElement" line="77" name="comment" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="string" doc="The string content of the comment.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="84" name="commentString" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_File" doc="The file that the comment exists in.&#10;&#10;@var PHP_CodeSniffer_File" line="91" name="phpcsFile" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="The word tokens that appear in the comment.&#10;&#10;Whitespace tokens also appear in this stack, but are separate tokens&#10;from words.&#10;&#10;@var array(string)" line="101" name="words" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="An array of all tags found in the comment.&#10;&#10;@var array(string)" line="108" name="foundTags" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_DocElement" doc="The previous doc element that was processed.&#10;&#10;null if the current element being processed is the first element in the&#10;doc comment.&#10;&#10;@var PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_DocElement" line="118" name="previousElement" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="A list of see elements that appear in this doc comment.&#10;&#10;@var array(PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_SingleElement)" line="125" name="sees" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="A list of see elements that appear in this doc comment.&#10;&#10;@var array(PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_SingleElement)" line="132" name="deprecated" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="A list of see elements that appear in this doc comment.&#10;&#10;@var array(PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_SingleElement)" line="139" name="links" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_SingleElement" doc="A element to represent \@since tags.&#10;&#10;@var PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_SingleElement" line="146" name="since" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="boolean" doc="True if the comment has been parsed.&#10;&#10;@var boolean" line="153" name="_hasParsed" /><variable attributes="private static" citdl="array" doc="The tags that this class can process.&#10;&#10;@var array(string)" line="165" name="_tags" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="array" doc="An array of unknown tags.&#10;&#10;@var array(string)" line="172" name="unknown" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="array" doc="The order of tags.&#10;&#10;@var array(string)" line="179" name="orders" /><scope attributes="public __ctor__" doc="Constructs a Doc Comment Parser.&#10;&#10;@param string               $comment   The comment to parse.&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile The file that this comment is in." ilk="function" line="188" lineend="193" name="__construct" signature="__construct(string $comment, PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="188" name="comment" /><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_File" ilk="argument" line="188" name="phpcsFile" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Initiates the parsing of the doc comment.&#10;&#10;@return void&#10;@throws PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_ParserException If the parser finds a&#10;                                                      problem with the&#10;                                                      comment." ilk="function" line="204" lineend="210" name="parse" signature="void parse()" /><scope attributes="private" doc="Parse the comment.&#10;&#10;@param string $comment The doc comment to parse.&#10;&#10;@return void&#10;@see _parseWords()" ilk="function" line="221" lineend="254" name="_parse" signature="void _parse(string $comment)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="221" name="comment" /><variable citdl="preg_split()" line="246" name="words" /><variable line="240" name="flags" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" citdl="substr()" line="225" name="line" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="224" name="lines" /></scope><scope attributes="private" doc="Parses each word within the doc comment.&#10;&#10;@return void&#10;@see _parse()&#10;@throws PHP_CodeSniffer_CommentParser_ParserException If more than the allowed&#10;                                                      number of occurences of&#10;                                                      a tag is found." ilk="function" line="266" lineend="379" name="_parseWords" signature="void _parseWords()"><variable citdl="boolean" line="270" name="prevTagPos" /><variable citdl="numWords" line="354" name="endPos" /><variable citdl="substr()" line="279" name="tag" /><variable citdl="substr()" line="303" name="prevTag" /><variable citdl="implode()" line="371" name="content" /><variable citdl="array_keys()" line="269" name="allowedTagNames" /><variable citdl="boolean" line="271" name="wordWasEmpty" /><variable citdl="array_slice()" line="370" name="tokens" /><variable citdl="count()" line="353" name="numWords" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="273" name="word" /><variable citdl="array()" line="332" name="knownTags" /><variable line="273" name="wordPos" /><variable line="268" name="allowedTags" /></scope><scope attributes="protected" doc="Returns the line that the token exists on in the doc comment.&#10;&#10;@param int $tokenPos The position in the words stack to find the line&#10;                     number for.&#10;&#10;@return int" ilk="function" line="390" lineend="399" name="getLine" returns="int" signature="int getLine(int $tokenPos)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="390" name="tokenPos" /><variable line="393" name="i" /><variable citdl="int" line="392" name="newlines" /></scope><scope attributes="protected" doc="Parses see tag element within the doc comment.&#10;&#10;